In the pursuit of getting OpenThread running multiple instances in parallel, I have found a fairly big issue with mbedtls. Take this code for example:

```
MbedTls::MbedTls(void)
{
    mbedtls_memory_buffer_alloc_init(mMemory, sizeof(mMemory));
}
```

That sets some global variables to use this class's private memory buffer. When you have multiple instances, they all end up calling this same code. If you happen to bring up a new instance in the middle of the previous one's operation, you completely reset that instance's buffer. Best case, if you bring up all instances at the same time and shut them down at the same time (which is what we do for python cert tests) you now only have 1 buffer's worth of memory to use for all instances, not to mention that you now have two separate threads accessing the same buffer, with no locks. At the current size of `2048 * sizeof(void*)` that isn't enough to pass the basic commissioning tests (though upping it to `2500` seems to fix it).

I have looked at mbedtls's code and it is infeasible to change it to support instancing. The only other option I could think of would be somehow correct OpenThread's usage of mbedtls use one global, static buffer or implement the alloc/free functions themselves.

Any thoughts?

#### Issue description

When using the ``PYBIND11_OVERLOAD`` macro, the compiler MSVC 14 2015 chokes when the output type is something like ``std::pair<double, double>`` and yields an obscure error about a problem with a "*" symbol.  I suspect the same problem would manifest with most STL types.  A workaround is a typedef which seems to placate the compiler

#### Reproducible example code

**Bad**:
``` C++
class PyVLEIsolineTracer : public VLEIsolineTracer {
public:
    /* Inherit the constructors */
    using VLEIsolineTracer::VLEIsolineTracer;

    std::pair<double, double> get_integration_limits() override {
        // Release the GIL
        py::gil_scoped_release release;
        {
            // Acquire GIL before calling Python code
            py::gil_scoped_acquire acquire;

            // Parameters to macro are: Return type, parent class, name of function in C++, argument(s)
            PYBIND11_OVERLOAD(std::pair<double, double>, 
                              VLEIsolineTracer, 
                              get_integration_limits, 
                              // No arguments
                              );
        }
    }
};
```

**Good**:
``` C++
class PyVLEIsolineTracer : public VLEIsolineTracer {
public:
    /* Inherit the constructors */
    using VLEIsolineTracer::VLEIsolineTracer;

    std::pair<double, double> get_integration_limits() override {
        // Release the GIL
        py::gil_scoped_release release;
        {
            // Acquire GIL before calling Python code
            py::gil_scoped_acquire acquire;

            // Parameters to macro are: Return type, parent class, name of function in C++, argument(s)
            typedef std::pair<double, double> pairdoubledouble;
            PYBIND11_OVERLOAD(pairdoubledouble, 
                              VLEIsolineTracer, 
                              get_integration_limits, 
                              // No arguments
                              );
        }
    }
};
```

